  -- `g\`: Toggle trash (`actions.toggle_trash`)

* Folding  Tags in LazyVim
** To fold HTML tags in LazyVim, you can use the following keymaps:
   -- `za`: Toggle fold
   -- `zc`: Close fold
   -- `zC`: Close all folds
   -- `zo`: Open fold
   -- `zO`: Open all folds
   -- `zr`: Reduce folding level by one
   -- `zR`: Open all folds recursively
   -- `zm`: More folding
   -- `zM`: Close all folds recursively

These keymaps work in normal mode (`n`). So, for example, if you want to toggle a fold, you'd press `za` while in normal mode with your cursor positioned over the line containing the HTML tag you want to fold.

